%20and%20patronage%20was%20completely%20transformed%20by%20the%20British%20into%20one%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fem%3E%20relationship%20of%20bribery%20and%20tribute%2C%20that%20aided%20their%20commercial%20and%20capitalist%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20are%20witnessing%20in%20India%20today%20with%20the%20decolonialisation%20talk%20strikingly%20mirrors%20Cohn%E2%80%99s%20assessment%20of%20British%20colonial%20practices%2C%20if%20only%20in%20a%20reverse%20manner.%20To%20avoid%20being%20seen%20as%20disturbing%20prevailing%20social%20relations%20chastened%20by%20their%20experience%20of%201857%2C%20the%20colonisers%20retained%20the%20imaginary%20spectacle%20of%20the%20Mughal%20court%20to%20cover%20up%20the%20fundamental%20break%20that%20they%20had%20instituted%20in%20the%20symbolic%20world.%20Exactly%20the%20opposite%20can%20be%20discerned%20in%20the%20sudden%20noise%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Edecolonising%20law%20codes%3C%2Fa%3E%2076%20years%20after%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence.%20The%20proposed%20exercise%20of%20indigenising%20laws%20%E2%80%93%20insincere%20at%20best%20and%20dangerous%20at%20worst%20%E2%80%93%20would%20only%20bring%20about%20a%20surface-level%20change%20of%20the%20imaginary%20through%20a%20spectacular%20show%20of%20rejecting%20the%20colonial%20inheritance%20while%20harbouring%20no%20aspirations%20for%20freedom%20at%20the%20structural%20and%20systemic%20level%20of%20the%20symbolic%20order%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECriminal%20law%20and%20justice%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20new%20Bills%20were%20recently%20introduced%20in%20Parliament%20by%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20of%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20to%20overhaul%20the%20criminal%20legal%20system%20that%20has%20been%20in%20existence%20since%20the%20colonial%20period.%20Colonial-era%20laws%20including%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%2C%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20and%20the%20updated%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20of%201973%20are%20set%20to%20be%20repealed%20and%20replaced%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%20and%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20respectively.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fthe-bills-in-perspective-8888597%2F%5C%22%3Eexpert%20analysts%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20last%20few%20days%20have%20suggested%2C%20these%20Bills%2C%20despite%20their%20grand%20posturing%2C%20largely%20keep%20intact%20the%20inherited%20legal%20edifice%20while%20introducing%20minimal%20changes%20to%20undo%20its%20multiple%20crises%20in%20the%20areas%20of%20police%20and%20prison%20reforms%2C%20and%20vaguely%20drafted%20laws%20and%20their%20arbitrary%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20dealing%20a%20blow%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20linguistic%20plurality%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindi-imposition-modi-govts-nomenclature-for-new-criminal-law-bills-stirs-row%5C%22%3Eprioritising%20Sanskritised%20Hindi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20their%20titles%20also%20misrepresent%20the%20point%20and%20purpose%20of%20these%20laws.%20For%20instance%2C%20by%20translating%20%E2%80%98penal%E2%80%99%20as%20%E2%80%98nyaya%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20commonly%20associated%20with%20justice%20in%20classical%20Hindu%20philosophy%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Bills%20reduces%20the%20latter%20to%20a%20much%20narrower%20concern%20with%20crime%20and%20punishment.%20It%20is%20anybody%E2%80%99s%20guess%20why%20this%20particular%20term%20was%20selected%2C%20but%20in%20their%202019%20election%20manifesto%2C%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20had%20come%20up%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Nyuntam%20Aay%20Yojana%E2%80%99%2C%20also%20called%20Nyay%2C%20that%20is%20the%20basic%20income%20scheme.%20Although%20not%20adequate%20for%20the%20universalisation%20of%20welfare%2C%20this%20gesture%20was%20at%20least%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20worldwide%20trend%20among%20political%20theorists%20to%20think%20about%20justice%20through%20the%20question%20of%20social%20redistribution.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20takes%20a%20step%20back%20in%20robbing%20justice%20of%20its%20redistributive%20thrust%20and%20equating%20it%20with%20the%20corrective%20problem%20of%20maintaining%20law%20and%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUCC%20and%20social%20difference%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelative%20to%20this%20new%20development%20in%20the%20field%20of%20criminal%20law%2C%20a%20longstanding%20pet%20project%20of%20the%20BJP%20which%20it%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20actualise%20thus%20far%20is%20the%20elimination%20of%20religion-based%20personal%20family%20laws%20and%20the%20enactment%20of%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code%20(UCC)%20applicable%20to%20all%20citizens%20throughout%20the%20country.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20normative%20pluralism%20of%20state%20and%20non-state%20laws%20on%20issues%20of%20marriage%2C%20divorce%20and%20inheritance%20as%20we%20know%20it%20today%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Funiform-civil-code-needed-to-decolonise-indian-family-law%2Farticleshow%2F102784639.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ecolonial%20product%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20far%20from%20being%20an%20exposition%20of%20the%20much-reviled%20policy%20of%20%E2%80%98divide%20and%20rule%E2%80%99%2C%20legal%20pluralism%20was%20initially%20in%20the%2018th%20century%20driven%20by%20Indophilia%2C%20and%20subsequently%20since%20the%20Queen%E2%80%99s%20Proclamation%20of%201858%2C%20by%20a%20sheer%20strategic%20necessity%20to%20maintain%20imperial%20dominion%20through%20the%20preservation%20of%20social%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20British%20motivation%20may%20have%20been%20with%20regard%20to%20respecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20heterogenous%20social%20life%2C%20anti-colonial%20thinkers%20had%20for%20the%20longest%20time%20separated%20their%20trenchant%20attack%20on%20the%20colonial%20administrative%20apparatus%20from%20a%20more%20affirmative%20orientation%20towards%20the%20empire%20as%20a%20political%20form.%20This%20is%20because%20unlike%20a%20European-style%20nation-state%2C%20an%20empire%20could%20conceptually%20hold%20together%20religious%20and%20cultural%20differences%20without%20erasing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20only%20in%201929%20that%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20adopted%20the%20famous%20Lahore%20resolution%20for%20%3Cem%3Epurna%20swaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20complete%20independence%2C%20as%20the%20nationalists%20finally%20understood%20that%20India%20had%20no%20future%20in%20an%20empire%20which%20could%20not%20serve%20as%20an%20effective%20counterweight%20to%20colonial%20exploitation.%20Yet%2C%20even%20when%20British%20rule%20gave%20way%20to%20a%20new%20nation-state%2C%20there%20remained%20a%20deep%20intellectual%20investment%20in%20ancient%20and%20medieval%20imperial%20figures%20such%20as%20Ashoka%20and%20Akbar%2C%20who%20were%20resurrected%20through%20the%20adoption%20of%20iconographic%20motifs%20and%20history%20writing.%20Although%20nationalism%20inevitably%20had%20a%20homogenising%20influence%2C%20the%20celebrated%20idea%20of%20India%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20%E2%80%98unity%20in%20diversity%E2%80%99%20drawn%20from%20the%20imperial%20past%20sought%20to%20keep%20open%20some%20of%20its%20closures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%5C%22%3EHow%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20UCC%20is%20ever%20brought%20into%20force%20in%20all%20sincerity%2C%20it%20certainly%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20nationalise%20India%E2%80%99s%20legal%20landscape%20which%20would%20then%20be%20disconnected%20altogether%20from%20the%20long%20imperial%20history%20of%20accommodating%20religious%20and%20cultural%20pluralism.%20Without%20in%20any%20way%20giving%20a%20pass%20to%20personal%20laws%20which%20perpetuate%20discriminatory%20practices%20against%20women%2C%20it%20must%20however%20be%20emphasised%20as%20has%20amply%20been%20done%20in%20feminist%20scholarship%20and%20activism%2C%20that%20legal%20uniformity%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbjp-ucc-with-gender-justice-discrimination-personal-laws%5C%22%3Enot%20the%20same%20as%20gender%20justice%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProgressive%20decolonisation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20movement%20of%20decolonisation%20stemmed%20from%20an%20ardently%20progressive%20impulse%20to%20compel%20European%20empires%20to%20reckon%20with%20their%20violent%20histories%20of%20slavery%20and%20racism%20that%20continue%20to%20mar%20previously%20colonised%20societies%20even%20today.%20But%20in%20India%2C%20the%20decoloniality%20discourse%20has%20been%20appropriated%20by%20Hindu%20nationalism%20which%20extends%20it%20back%20to%20the%20800%20years%20of%20Muslim%20imperial%20rule%2C%20with%20an%20intensely%20parochial%20and%20superficial%20programme%20of%20indigenisation.%20Those%20committed%20to%20a%20forward-looking%20left-liberal%20politics%20must%20pause%20and%20wonder%20whether%20deploying%20this%20language%20which%20has%20been%20entirely%20co-opted%20by%20their%20ideological%20antagonists%20can%20at%20all%20serve%20any%20emancipatory%20purpose%20in%20the%20current%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20decolonisation%20so%20attractive%20to%20Hindutva%20is%20its%20negative%20and%20reactionary%20side%2C%20which%20enables%20enjoyment%20simply%20from%20demolition%20and%20destruction%20of%20all%20kinds%20%E2%80%93%20from%20architecture%20to%20law%20codes.%20This%20is%20a%20complete%20repudiation%20of%20the%20legacy%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%99s%20founders%2C%20whose%20anticolonial%20politics%20was%20always%20supplemented%20by%20a%20more%20positive%20world-making%20imagination%20directed%20towards%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemocracy%20and%20the%20foreign%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20times%2C%20the%20key%20marker%20of%20nationalism%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20rejection%20of%20everything%20that%20is%20foreign%20including%20the%20English%20language%20and%20even%20the%20Constitution%2C%20much%20of%20which%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Ftheres-a-case-for-we-the-people-to-embrace-a-new-constitution-11692021963182.html%5C%22%3Eapparently%20derived%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%201935.%20One%20way%20to%20respond%20would%20of%20course%20be%20to%20argue%20that%20Indians%20have%20owned%20up%20to%20English%20and%20the%20Constitution%20despite%20the%20colonial%20origins%20through%20continuous%20usage%20and%20customisation.%20But%2C%20more%20fundamentally%2C%20as%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20thinkers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fpaperback%2F9780691114767%2Fdemocracy-and-the-foreigner%5C%22%3ERousseau%20to%20Freud%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20indicated%2C%20a%20degree%20of%20foreignness%20is%20elemental%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20democratic%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20decolonial%20posturing%20is%20to%20nativise%20the%20legal%20system%2C%20the%20hidden%20impulse%20driving%20this%20project%20is%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20society%20governed%20by%20law.%20Instead%2C%20what%20takes%20its%20place%20is%20the%20superegoic%20pressure%20of%20collective%20conscience%20and%20majoritarian%20justice.%20Lost%20in%20the%20debate%20about%20the%20British%20or%20Indian%20origins%20of%20our%20legal%20codes%2C%20is%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20inherently%20alienating%20capacity.%20Law%20forces%20people%20out%20of%20their%20immediate%20context%20of%20family%20and%20kinship%2C%20and%20enables%20them%20to%20forge%20a%20life%20in%20common%20with%20non-identical%20others.%20Even%20in%20this%20distressing%20period%20for%20the%20republic%2C%20we%20must%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20defy%20the%20nativist%20urge%2C%20as%20it%20is%20only%20through%20some%20kind%20of%20self-alienation%20that%20Indians%20can%20form%20a%20real%20political%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Moiz%20Tundawala%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20Jindal%20Global%20Law%20School%2C%20Delhi%20NCR%2C%20India%20and%20Dr%20Salmoli%20Choudhuri%20is%20an%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692945041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24135018%2FF3ZJcv4aoAEfWJn.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdoes-todays-india-need-decolonisation-speak%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20proposed%20exercise%20of%20indigenising%20criminal%20laws%20%E2%80%93%20insincere%20at%20best%20and%20dangerous%20at%20worst%20%E2%80%93%20would%20only%20bring%20about%20a%20surface-level%20change%20of%20the%20imaginary%20through%20a%20spectacular%20show%20of%20rejecting%20the%20colonial%20inheritance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdoes-todays-india-need-decolonisation-speak%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWorld%20Has%20To%20Grow%20With%20Equity%2C%20Inclusiveness%26quot%3B%3A%20G20%20Sherpa%20Amitabh%20Kant%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692944940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F9b83i31_amitabh-kant-ndtv-650_650x400_25_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%