ars%20have%20given%20us%20ample%20reasons%20for%20why%20self%20defense%20is%20an%20important%20part%20of%20training%20for%20flight%20attendants%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20Garland%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Association%20of%20Flight%20Attendants%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F20%2Fflight-attendants-training-union-00111864%5C%22%3Etold%20Politico%20in%20a%20report%20published%20August%2020%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Association%20of%20Flight%20Attendants%20has%20demanded%20more%20self-defense%20training%20for%20crew%20since%202005%2C%20including%20a%20provision%20in%20a%20new%20US%20Senate%20aviation%20bill%20requiring%20airlines%20to%20give%20flight%20attendants%20training%20on%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Bsubdue%20and%20restrain%26quot%3B%20passengers%2C%20per%20Politico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increasing%20trend%20of%20unruly%20passenger%20incidents%20is%20worrying.%20Passengers%20and%20crew%20are%20entitled%20to%20a%20safe%20and%20hassle-free%20experience%20on%20board%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iata.org%2Fen%2Fpressroom%2F2023-releases%2F2023-06-04-02%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20Conrad%20Clifford%2C%20a%20deputy%20director%20general%20of%20the%20IATA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20excuse%20for%20not%20following%20the%20instructions%20of%20the%20crew.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMacDonald%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-pilot-lashed-out-abrasive-customers-flight-attendants-not-server-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692935969000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e81657a7adf7001907987e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-pilot-lashed-out-abrasive-customers-flight-attendants-not-server-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20was%20one%20unruly%20incident%20reported%20for%20every%20568%20flights%20in%202022%2C%20which%20marked%20an%20increase%20from%20one%20incident%20for%20every%20835%20flights%20in%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kteo%40insider.com%20(Kai%20Xiang%20Teo)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-pilot-lashed-out-abrasive-customers-flight-attendants-not-server-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22State%E2%80%99s%20Discretionary%20Power%20Is%20Opposed%20to%20the%20Vision%20of%20the%20Freedom%20Struggle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25090738%2F428r1954_0.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20India%20enters%20its%2077th%20year%20of%20Independence%2C%20there%20is%20much%20to%20celebrate.%20India%20not%20only%20survived%20the%20challenges%20of%20poverty%2C%20religious%20strife%2C%20caste%20and%20secession%2C%20it%20has%20thrived.%20It%20punched%20well%20above%20its%20weight%20in%20global%20and%20economic%20affairs%2C%20as%20a%20chief%20negotiator%20in%20major%20conflicts%20like%20the%20Korean%20War%2C%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20pharmacy%2C%20as%20an%20IT%20hub%2C%20and%20as%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economies.%20From%20the%20trauma%20of%20Partition%20and%20colonialism%2C%20the%20country%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way.%20There%20is%20much%20more%20to%20be%20done%20if%20India%20is%20to%20fulfil%20the%20aims%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20and%20support%20the%20aspirations%20of%20its%201.4%20billion%20citizens.%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20Indian%20State%E2%80%99s%20design%2C%20which%20enables%20it%20to%20effectively%20centralise%20power%20and%20promote%20expediency%20over%20process%2C%20undermines%20its%20successes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20freedom%20struggle%20was%20novel%20in%20its%20commitment%20to%20non-violent%20protest%20and%20in%20emphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20process%20in%20achieving%20an%20aim.%20This%20played%20out%20especially%20during%20the%20First%20Non-Cooperation%20Movement%20in%201922%2C%20when%20it%20looked%20likely%20that%20British%20rule%20would%20collapse%2C%20but%20Gandhi%20called%20off%20the%20agitation%20because%20of%20the%20Chauri%20Chaura%20incident%2C%20in%20which%20a%20mob%20burned%20down%20a%20police%20station%20on%20February%204%2C%201922.%20Gandhi%20called%20off%20the%20agitation%2C%20and%20his%20arrest%20followed.%20This%20incident%20had%20a%20clear%20lesson%20for%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20%E2%80%95%20the%20means%20are%20as%20important%20as%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20Independence%2C%20the%20trauma%20of%20Partition%2C%20the%20integration%20of%20the%20princely%20states%20and%20widespread%20poverty%20resulted%20in%20a%20constitutional%20setup%20where%20the%20Union%20government%20could%20convert%20the%20country%20into%20a%20unitary%20state%20and%20override%20fundamental%20rights.%20The%20State%20can%20exercise%20such%20powers%20through%20emergency%20provisions%2C%20the%20office%20of%20the%20governor%2C%20money%20bills%2C%20ordinances%20and%20more.%20These%20centralising%20powers%20that%20legally%20bypass%20established%20processes%20have%20outlived%20their%20purpose%3B%20a%20transfer%20of%20power%20away%20from%20the%20Union%20to%20lower%20tiers%20of%20government%20is%20needed%20to%20deepen%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20posed%20by%20such%20centralisation%20and%20discretionary%20powers%20was%20clear%20under%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20through%20the%20combination%20of%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Internal%20Security%20Act%20(MISA)%2C%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20the%20imposition%20of%20internal%20Emergency%20checks%20on%20democracy%20and%20executive%20action%20to%20support%20political%20aims.%20Since%20Independence%2C%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20has%20been%20invoked%20121%20times%2C%20more%20often%20than%20not%20to%20support%20political%20goals%20rather%20than%20to%20resolve%20a%20genuine%20crisis.%20It%20was%20used%20about%2070%20times%20between%201966%20and%201984.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20which%20was%20conceived%20as%20a%20way%20to%20support%20fledgling%20state%20governments%2C%20is%20now%20a%20convenient%20tool%20of%20control%20for%20the%20Union%20against%20Opposition-ruled%20states.%20The%20wide%20ambit%20of%20powers%20provided%20to%20them%2C%20including%20withholding%20assent%20through%20pocket%20vetoes%20or%20forwarding%20them%20to%20the%20President%20for%20review%2C%20hinders%20the%20functioning%20of%20state%20governments.%20For%20example%2C%2019%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20West%20Bengal%20government%2C%20dating%20back%20to%202016%2C%20still%20require%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20assent%20in%20order%20to%20become%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20times%2C%20such%20as%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20Union%20was%20able%20to%20bypass%20the%20federal%20structure%20by%20unilaterally%20imposing%20a%20lockdown%20under%20the%20Disaster%20Management%20Act%20(2006)%20and%20Epidemic%20Diseases%20Act%20(1897)%2C%20which%20allowed%20it%20to%20suspend%20the%20free%20movement%20of%20people%20and%20amend%20the%20Essential%20Commodities%20Act%20without%20any%20Parliamentary%20or%20state%20oversight%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Seventh%20Schedule%20lists%20health%20as%20a%20state%20subject.%20Such%20centralising%20tendencies%20underscore%20the%20ease%20with%20which%20the%20state%20can%2C%20if%20it%20desires%2C%20bypass%20constitutional%20processes%20to%20achieve%20an%20aim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tussle%20between%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20state%20control%20usually%20veers%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20state.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20Articles%2014-21%20of%20the%20Constitution%20enshrine%20all%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20liberties.%20This%20is%20countered%20through%20the%20use%20of%20preventive%20detention%2C%20arbitrary%20arrests%20and%20raids.%20When%20abused%2C%20these%20provisions%20enable%20the%20state%20to%20prioritise%20political%20aims%20over%20due%20process%2C%20as%20seen%20with%20the%20sedition%20clause%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20the%20use%20of%20economic%20offences%20under%20the%20IT%20Act%20and%20FERA%2C%20the%20misuse%20of%20preventive%20detention%20laws%20spanning%20governments%2C%20from%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Internal%20Security%20Act%20(MISA)%20to%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act.%20These%20laws%20may%20have%20a%20place%20in%20the%20Union%2C%20and%20should%20be%20used%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20cases%2C%20with%20clear%20thresholds%20in%20place%20to%20prevent%20their%20abuse.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20declaration%20of%20Emergency%20must%20be%20ratified%20by%202%2F3rds%20of%20Parliament%20to%20be%20enforceable%2C%20only%20after%20which%20fundamental%20rights%20can%20be%20suspended%2C%20that%20too%20for%20six%20months%3B%20a%20similar%20mechanism%20that%20creates%20prevailing%20conditions%20to%20implement%20such%20laws%20might%20find%20a%20balance%20between%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20national%20security%2C%20while%20ensuring%20that%20due%20process%20is%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeventy-six%20years%20after%20Independence%2C%20the%20Indian%20republic%20has%20grown%20and%20adapted%20to%20a%20host%20of%20challenges.%20It%20successfully%20integrated%20a%20divided%20and%20broken%20country%20and%20built%20its%20foundations.%20It%20improved%20the%20quality%20of%20public%20health%20and%20education%20and%20has%20empowered%20all%20its%20citizens%20with%20some%20basic%20democratic%20rights.%20The%20state%E2%80%99s%20discretionary%20powers%20lie%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20vision%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%2C%20which%20was%20born%20out%20non-violent%20protest%20that%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20ends%20do%20not%20justify%20the%20means%3B%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20powers%20must%20move%20to%20local%20levels%20of%20government%20and%20to%20ordinary%20citizens%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20ideals%20of%20Independence%20are%20fully%20upheld.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVibhav%20Mariwala%20studied%20History%20and%20Anthropology%20at%20Stanford%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692934707000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25090738%2F428r1954_0.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fstates-discretionary-power-is-opposed-to-the-vision-of-the-freedom-struggle%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20state%E2%80%99s%20powers%20must%20move%20to%20local%20levels%20of%20government%20and%20to%20ordinary%20citizens%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20ideals%20of%20Independence%20are%20fully%20upheld.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fstates-discretionary-power-is-opposed-to-the-vision-of-the-freedom-struggle%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Says%20Modi%20Raised%20Border%20in%20'Conversation'%20With%20Xi%2C%20China%20Says%20'Indian%20Request%20Led%20to%20Informal%20Talks'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F10123822%2FModi-with-Xi-Jinping.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%20their%20first%20direct%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20in%20over%20nine%20months%2C%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20seemed%20to%20have%20remained%20at%20their%20respective%20positions%20on%20the%20border%20standoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20publicly%20claimed%20that%20the%20informal%20talks%20was%20based%20on%20an%20Indian%20request.%20While%20there%20was%20no%20official%20denial%20from%20New%20Delhi%2C%20sources%20claimed%20that%20there%20had%20been%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpending%E2%80%9D%20request%20from%20China%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbilateral%20meeting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20leaders%20talked%20on%20Wednesday%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit%2C%20but%20both%20sides%20waited%20for%20nearly%20a%20day%20before%20declaring%20that%20there%20had%20been%20an%20interaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20took%20the%20lead%20in%20this%20announcement%2C%20as%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20revealed%2C%20shortly%20before%20their%20departure%20from%20South%20Africa%2C%20that%20Modi%20had%20conversed%20with%20the%20Chinese%20president.%20This%20was%20their%20first%20direct%20conversation%20that%20has%20been%20revealed%20publicly%20since%20they%20apparently%20exchanged%20remarks%20in%20November%202022%20in%20Indonesia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKwatra%20volunteered%20that%20the%20two%20leaders%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconversation%E2%80%9D%20A%20few%20hours%20later%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccandid%20and%20in-depth%20exchange%20of%20views%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20took%20place%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20Indian%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20Kwatra%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20Xi%20Jinping%20of%20China%2C%20prime%20minister%20highlighted%20India%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20on%20the%20unresolved%20issues%20along%20the%20LAC%20on%20the%20western%20sector%20of%20the%20border%20areas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stated%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%9Cunderlined%20that%20the%20maintenance%20of%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20at%20borders%20and%20observing%20and%20respecting%20the%20LAC%20are%20essential%20for%20the%20normalisation%20of%20India%20China%20relationship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20Indian%20diplomat%20then%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20an%20understanding%20from%20both%20leaders%20for%20an%20early%20resolution%20of%20the%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20agreed%20to%20direct%20their%20relevant%20officials%20to%20intensify%20their%20efforts%20at%20expeditious%20disengagement%20and%20de-escalation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20did%20not%20mention%20when%20and%20where%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconversation%E2%80%9D%20took%20place%20%E2%80%93%20or%20who%20made%20the%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPresident%20Xi%20Jinping%20talked%20with%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%20at%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20request%20on%20August%2023%2C%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Feng%2Fxwfw_665399%2Fs2510_665401%2F202308%2Ft20230825_11132463.html%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20asked%20if%20they%20had%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%2C%20Kwatra%20once%20more%20described%20the%20interaction%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconversation%E2%80%9D%2C%20indicating%20that%20New%20Delhi%20does%20not%20want%20imply%20that%20it%20was%20formal%20and%20structured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20differed%2C%20emphasising%20that%20the%20interaction%20was%20substantive.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20two%20leaders%20had%20a%20candid%20and%20in-depth%20exchange%20of%20views%20on%20current%20China-India%20relations%20and%20other%20questions%20of%20shared%20interest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20emphasised%20that%20the%20talks%20were%20requested%20by%20India%20in%20a%20public%20statement.%20There%20was%20an%20Indian%20reaction%20shared%20with%20the%20media%2C%20but%20it%20was%20made%20off%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20pending%20request%20from%20the%20Chinese%20side%20for%20a%20bilateral%20meeting.%20The%20two%20leaders%2C%20however%2C%20had%20an%20informal%20conversation%20in%20the%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Lounge%20during%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20official%20Indian%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20response%20from%20Indian%20sources%20does%20not%20deny%20that%20the%20latest%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20was%20based%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20request.%20It%20stated%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20request%20for%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cpending%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20did%20not%20mention%20when%20it%20had%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20side%20doubled%20down%20on%20its%20insistence%20that%20it%20was%20not%20a%20structured%20meeting%20held%20in%20a%20separate%20room%2C%20by%20stating%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20informal%20conversation%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20BRICS%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20lounge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20and%20Xi%20together%20participated%20in%20various%20BRICS%20events%20for%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20last%20three%20days.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20took%20part%20in%20two%20sessions%20of%20the%20main%20plenary%20during%20the%20day%20and%20also%20attended%20the%20official%20dinner%20in%20the%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20each%20country%20presented%20the%20content%20of%20their%20conversation%20once%20again%20highlighted%20the%20divergence%20in%20perspective%20concerning%20the%20ongoing%20border%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPresident%20Xi%20stressed%20that%20improving%20China-India%20relations%20serves%20the%20common%20interests%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20and%20peoples%2C%20and%20is%20also%20conducive%20to%20peace%2C%20stability%20and%20development%20of%20the%20world%20and%20the%20region.%20The%20two%20sides%20should%20bear%20in%20mind%20the%20overall%20interests%20of%20their%20bilateral%20relations%20and%20handle%20properly%20the%20border%20issue%20so%20as%20to%20jointly%20safeguard%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20in%20the%20border%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20the%20Indian%20statement%2C%20the%20Chinese%20rendition%20omitted%20any%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunresolved%20issues%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20LAC.%20Neither%20did%20it%20mention%20that%20there%20was%20an%20agreement%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20towards%20%E2%80%9Cexpeditious%20disengagement%20and%20de-escalation%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20stated%20by%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20also%20reiterated%20the%20Chinese%20view%20that%20the%20border%20stand-off%20should%20not%20impact%20the%20overall%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20president%20is%20expected%20to%20visit%20India%20in%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20for%20the%20annual%20G20%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%20have%20been%20in%20a%20military%20stand-off%20at%20multiple%20points%20on%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20since%20May%202020%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20death%20of%2020%20Indian%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20military%20and%20diplomatic%20talks%2C%20there%20has%20been%20withdrawal%20of%20troops%20at%20around%20four%20friction%20points%20which%20has%20led%20to%20creation%20of%20buffer%20zones%20where%20neither%20country%20is%20allowed%20to%20patrol.%20It%20essentially%20meant%20that%20Indian%20army%20cannot%20patrol%20at%20around%2026%20patrolling%20points%20that%20they%20had%20access%20to%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20still%20two%20strategic%20points%20%E2%80%93%20Depsang%20Plains%20and%20Demchok%20%E2%80%93%20where%20India%20and%20China%20have%20been%20unable%20to%20reach%20any%20understanding.%20While%20India%20claimed%20that%20surge%20of%20Chinese%20troops%20at%20those%20points%20in%20these%20areas%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20three-year-old%20standoff%2C%20China%20insisted%20that%20these%20were%20legacy%20issues%20from%20the%20broader%20boundary%20dispute%20and%20should%20not%20be%20included%20in%20discussions%20concerning%20the%20ongoing%20border%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20last%20Friday%2C%20senior%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20military%20commanders%20have%20engaged%20in%20a%20series%20of%20back-to-back%20discussions%20at%20the%20Major%20General%20level%20that%20were%20seen%20as%20a%20scene-setter%20for%20a%20much-anticipated%20bilateral%20meeting%20between%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20at%20BRICS%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foreign%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20mention%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20was%20a%20change%20from%20the%20situation%20last%20time%20when%20the%20two%20leaders%20had%20talked%20with%20each%20other%20at%20the%20dinner%20for%20G20%20summit%20in%20Bali.%20Despite%20a%20photo%20surfacing%20of%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20standing%20and%20talking%20with%20each%20other%2C%20Kwatra%20had%20then%20only%20mentioned%20that%20there%20was%20an%20exchange%20of%20pleasantries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20China%20had%20not%20mentioned%20the%20encounter%20then%2C%20Chinese%20foreign%20minister%20Wang%20Yi%20referred%20to%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20consensus%20stabilising%20China-India%20relations%20in%20Bali%E2%80%9D%20at%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwang-yi-ajit-doval-india-china-brics%5C%22%3Emeeting%20with%20Indian%20national%20security%20advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20that%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Feight-months-later-india-says-modi-xi-did-talk-about-stabilising-ties-at-bali-encounter%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20leader%20had%20%E2%80%9Cexchanged%20courtesies%20and%20also%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20to%20stabilise%20our%20bilateral%20relations%E2%80%9D%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20at%2011%20pm%20on%20August%2024%2C%202023%2C%20and%20was%20updated%20and%20republished%20at%209%20am%20on%20August%2025%2C%202023.%20It%20was%20once%20again%20updated%20with%20China%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20talks%20were%20based%20on%20Indian%20request.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692934234000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F10123822%2FModi-with-Xi-Jinping.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20has%20since%20publicly%20claimed%20that%20the%20informal%20talks%20was%20based%20on%20an%20Indian%20request.%20This%20was%20their%20first%20direct%20conversation%20that%20has%20been%20revealed%20publicly%20since%20they%20apparently%20exchanged%20remarks%20in%20November%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Afghanistan's%20Farooqi%20runs%20out%20'shocked'%20Shadab%20Khan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692933746000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103040800%2Cimgsize-37132.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fwatch-afghanistans-fazalhaq-farooqi-runs-out-shocked-shadab-khan%2Farticleshow%2F