ag%20Port%20Trust%20official.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20so%2C%20the%20state%20government%20began%20issuing%20warnings.%E2%80%9D%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20as%20yet%20clear%20who%20Krishnapatnam%20would%20go%20to.%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20think%20Jagan%20had%20anyone%20in%20his%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20retired%20IAS%20official.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20just%20wanted%20to%20take%20over%20the%20port.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20one%20of%20the%20winners%20from%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fvendetta-dominates-andhra-politics-under-jagan-s-rule-766122.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98vendetta%20politics%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20Jagan%20and%20the%20TDP%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20%3Ci%3EDeccan%20Herald%20%3C%2Fi%3Edescribed%20these%20events%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20Adani%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20government%20pressure%20by%20way%20of%20cancellation%20of%20projects%20mounted%2C%20the%20port%20executive%20said%2C%20the%20younger%20son%20of%20C.V.%20Rao%20agreed%20to%20sell%20his%20stake%20in%20Krishnapatnam%20to%20Adani.%20Shortly%20afterwards%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20family%20acquiesced%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20part%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20where%20Adani%20picked%20up%20a%2075%25%20stake%20in%20the%20port%2C%20was%20announced%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-krishnapatnam-port-m-a-apsez-idUSKBN1Z21D9%5C%22%3EJanuary%203%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20group%20acquired%20the%20rest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adaniports.com%2FNewsroom%2FMedia-Releases%2FAdani-Ports-increases-its-ownership-from-75-to-100-in-Krishnapatnam-Port%5C%22%3EApril%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20emailed%20questions%20to%20C.%20Sridhar%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Navayuga%20Engineering%2C%20the%20Adani%20group%2C%20and%20the%20office%20of%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%20seeking%20to%20better%20understand%20this%20process.%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20full%20response%20is%20appended%20below.%20It%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20specific%20questions%20about%20Gangavaram%20and%20Krishnapatnam%20but%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20business%20expansion%20decisions%20emerge%20from%20a%20careful%20evaluation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20the%20potential%20acquisition%2C%20its%20prospects%20for%20growth%20and%20its%20synergies%20with%20our%20existing%20operations%2C%20through%20fair%2C%20transparent%20and%20well-established%20business%20processes.%20These%20are%20business%20transactions%20handled%20professionally%2C%20with%20mutual%20respect%20and%20trust.%E2%80%9D%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20the%20others%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20tenure%20of%20Jagan%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20the%20ownership%20of%20a%20number%20of%20infrastructure%20projects%20appears%20to%20have%20moved%20to%20two%20sets%20of%20firms.%20The%20first%20is%20Adani.%20The%20second%20is%20to%20six%20or%20so%20political%20and%20business%20family%20dynasts%2C%20some%20of%20whom%2C%20like%20the%20Aurobindo%20group%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zaubacorp.com%2Fcompany%2FAUROBINDO-REALTY-INFRASTRUCTURE-PRIVATE-LIMITED%2FU45500TG2016PTC111433%5C%22%3Edirectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pressreader.com%2Findia%2Fdeccan-chronicle%2F20130508%2F282514361043106%5C%22%3Efamily%20links%20to%20leaders%20from%20Jagan%E2%80%99s%20party%2C%20the%20YSR%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20pertinent%20to%20mention%20here%20that%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%2C%20who%20has%20had%20no%20public%20association%20with%20the%20Adani%20Group%2C%20unlike%20the%20BJP%2C%20himself%20came%20to%20office%20with%20significant%20vulnerabilities.%20During%20the%20UPA%20years%2C%20he%20had%20been%20charged%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fjagan-received-rs-1172-crore-as-bribes-from-investors-cbi-38286%5C%22%3Eseveral%20corruption%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20his%20march%20across%20Andhra%2C%20he%20was%20out%20on%20bail.%20This%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20perception%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20leverage%20over%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20wrote%20to%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%20asking%20him%20to%20comment%20on%20these%20aspects.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20he%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98A%20decision%20made%20independently%2C%20without%20any%20external%20pressure%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Krishnapatnam%20came%20Gangavaram%E2%80%99s%20turn.%20Unlike%20Navayuga%2C%20D.V.S.%20Raju%20had%20stayed%20aloof%20from%20politics.%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20however%2C%20had%20three%20private%20ports%20%E2%80%93%20Gangavaram%2C%20Krishnapatnam%20and%20Kakinada.%20Three%20more%20were%20coming%20up%20%E2%80%93%20Machilipatnam%2C%20Ramayapatnam%2C%20and%20another%20near%20Srikakulam.%20Of%20these%2C%20Aurobindo%20Realty%20had%20bagged%20Ramayapatnam%20and%20Kakinada.%20The%20state%20had%20cancelled%20Srikakulam%20and%20awarded%20Machilipatnam%20to%20Adani%2C%20who%20had%20also%20acquired%20Krishnapatnam.%20That%20left%20Gangavaram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdani%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fwebroot%2Fuploads%2Fdownload_audit_report%2F2013%2FAndhra_Pradesh_economic_sector_report_3_2013.pdf%5C%22%3Eput%20in%20a%20bid%20for%20Gangavaram%20in%202002%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20lost%20out%20to%20Raju.%20And%20in%202015%2C%20as%20we%20have%20described%20in%20Part%201%2C%20his%20talks%20with%20Raju%20to%20buy%20the%20port%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fuk%5C%22%3Efor%20a%20total%20consideration%20of%20%242.1%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20yield%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Adani%20tried%20again%20in%202021%2C%20however%2C%20he%20found%20Raju%20was%20willing%20to%20exit.%20Asked%20for%20the%20reason%20why%20they%20had%20now%20agreed%20to%20sell%2C%20the%20Raju%20family%20sent%20an%20emailed%20response.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20several%20years%2C%20we%20have%20been%20receiving%20many%20proposals%20from%20leading%20global%20port%20players%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20careful%20evaluation%2C%20we%20found%20synergies%20with%20Adani%20Ports%20and%20have%20taken%20a%20decision%20for%20merger%20and%20it%20was%20purely%20a%20business%20decision.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99s%20questionnaire%20to%20Raju%20included%20two%20allegations%20that%20a%20number%20of%20sources%20had%20made.%20First%2C%20that%20the%20Greater%20Visakhapatnam%20Municipal%20Corporation%E2%80%99s%20February%202021%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DQo2QFf3rw-M%5C%22%3Edemolish%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Gangavaram%20boundary%20wall%3C%2Fa%3E%20pursuant%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yovizag.com%2Fbc-road-connecting-gajuwaka-and-vizag-steel-plant-in-for-an-expansion%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20nine-year-old%20encroachment%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20local%20industries%20association%20had%20helped%20firm%20up%20the%20promoter%E2%80%99s%20mind%20to%20exit.%20And%20second%2C%20that%20soon%20after%20the%20demolition%2C%20a%20senior%20political%20figure%20in%20Jagan%E2%80%99s%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%20met%20him%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20sell.%20To%20these%20allegations%2C%20Raju%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20to%20emphasize%20that%20this%20decision%20was%20made%20independently%2C%20without%20any%20external%20pressure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20also%20wrote%20to%20Adani%20and%20chief%20minister%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20seeking%20their%20comments.%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20rejection%20of%20any%20allegations%20of%20state%20coercion%20has%20already%20been%20mentioned%20in%20this%20story.%20Its%20full%20response%2C%20as%20mentioned%20above%2C%20is%20appended%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20article.%20The%20political%20leader%20and%20the%20chief%20minister%20didn%E2%80%99t%20respond%20but%20Adityanath%20Das%2C%20who%20was%20chief%20secretary%20of%20Andhra%20at%20the%20time%2C%20also%20denied%20the%20government%20had%20played%20any%20role.%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20specific%20transaction%20between%20Gangavaram%20and%20Adani%2C%20we%20had%20no%20say%20on%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20state%20government%20side%2C%20there%20was%20no%20coercion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20weeks%20that%20followed%20the%20sale%2C%20the%20state%20government%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.itln.in%2Fapsez-concludes-acquisition-of-10-stake-in-gangavaram-port-for-645-cr-shipping%5C%22%3Esold%20its%20stake%20to%20Adani%20at%20the%20same%20valuation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20Gangavaram%20a%20fully-owned%20unit%20of%20Adani%20Ports%20%26amp%3B%20SEZ%20(APSEZ).%20It%20was%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20sell%20its%20stake%20%E2%80%93%20without%20calling%20for%20bidding%20%E2%80%93%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20PIL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24191752%2FKrishnapatnam_port_cranes_unloadng_a_ship.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24191752%2FKrishnapatnam_port_cranes_unloadng_a_ship.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24191752%2FKrishnapatnam_port_cranes_unloadng_a_ship-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24191752%2FKrishnapatnam_port_cranes_unloadng_a_ship-1024x681.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669657%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECranes%20unloading%20a%20ship%20at%20Krishnapatnam%20port.%20Photo%3A%20%E0%B0%B0%E0%B0%B9%E0%B1%8D%E0%B0%AE%E0%B0%BE%E0%B0%A8%E0%B1%81%E0%B0%A6%E0%B1%8D%E0%B0%A6%E0%B1%80%E0%B0%A8%E0%B1%8D%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EState%3C%2Fb%3E%E2%80%99%3Cb%3Es%20counter%20to%20the%20charge%20of%20forgoing%20revenue%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20counter-affidavit%2C%20signed%20by%20R.%20Karikal%20Valaven%2C%20special%20chief%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20(infrastructure%20and%20investment%20department)%2C%20the%20state%20government%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20has%20secured%20the%20best%20price%20on%20market%20considerations%20and%20there%20is%20no%20compromise%20on%20maximisation%20of%20revenues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20it%20had%20accepted%20the%20transaction%20between%20APSEZ%20and%20D.V.S.%20Raju%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%20of%20the%20original%20concession%20agreement%20would%20be%20retained.%20The%20state%20government%20cited%20a%20legal%20opinion%20from%20ex-CJI%20Dipak%20Misra%20saying%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Cno%20constitutional%20mandate%20for%20auction%20under%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20even%20though%20%E2%80%9Csale%20by%20public%20auction%20or%20by%20inviting%20tender%20is%20the%20ordinary%20rule%2C%20yet%20it%20is%20not%20an%20invariable%20rule..%20there%20can%20be%20exceptional%20circumstances%20which%20may%20necessitate%20departure%20from%20the%20ordinary%20rule%E2%80%A6%20The%20concept%20of%20holding%20an%20auction%20of%20shares%20of%20GPL%2C%20in%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20unquestionably%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20economic%20rationale.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20opinion%2C%20Misra%20also%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20cannot%20auction%20its%2010.4%25%20stake%20without%20offering%20the%20first%20right%20of%20refusal%20to%20the%20promoter%2C%20which%20is%20now%20APSEZ.%20He%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20marketability%20of%2010.4%25%20is%20very%20low%20as%20the%20role%20of%20a%20minority%20shareholder%20in%20a%20company%20is%20very%20minimal.%E2%80%9D%20Misra%20said%20that%20Warburg%E2%80%99s%20sale%20of%20shares%20to%20APSEZ%20was%20%E2%80%9Carrived%20at%20by%20way%20of%20an%20arm%E2%80%99s%20length%20transaction%20between%20two%20unrelated%20private%20parties%20and%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20ordinarily%20a%20fair%20transaction.%20It%E2%80%99s%20likely%20that%20a%20valuation%20now%20undertaken%20by%20GoAP%20will%20lead%20to%20similar%20value.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20allegation%20that%20the%20port%E2%80%99s%20land%20had%20been%20undervalued%2C%20the%20government%20counter%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20concession%20agreement%2C%20the%20(Andhra%20Pradesh%20Maritime%20Board)%20will%20be%20entitled%20to%20purchase%20the%20land%20after%20expiry%20of%20the%20Concession%20period%20by%20paying%20an%20amount%20calculated%20after%20factoring%206.5%25%20as%20an%20appreciation%20every%20year%E2%80%A6%20in%20such%20circumstances%2C%20the%20value%20attributed%20to%20the%20land%20by%20the%20petitioners%20and%20thereby%20jumping%20to%20conclusion%20that%20the%20State%20is%20parting%20with%20said%20land%20without%20any%20consideration%20in%20non-transparent%20manner%20is%20not%20tenable.%E2%80%9D%20In%20addition%2C%20KPMG%20told%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20considered%20the%20present%20value%20of%20the%20land%20escalated%20at%206.5%20per%20cent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvaluating%20the%20valuation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20question%20about%20whether%20Gangavaram%20had%20been%20correctly%20valued%2C%20the%20state%20government%20said%20it%20had%20asked%20KPMG%20to%20value%20Gangavaram%E2%80%99s%20shares%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20it%20had%20asked%20SBI%20Capital%20Markets%20to%20study%20whether%20it%20should%20sell%20its%20shares%20directly%20to%20Adani%20or%20call%20for%20an%20open%20bid.%20In%20its%20report%2C%20KPMG%20Valuation%20Services%20said%20it%20derived%20Gangavaram%E2%80%99s%20valuation%20by%2C%20among%20other%20methodologies%2C%20averaging%20EV%2FEBITDA%20multiples%20of%2014%20%E2%80%9Ccomparable%E2%80%9D%20ports.%20(It%20used%20discounted%20cash%20flow%2C%20comparable%20port%20valuations%2C%20comparable%20transactions%20and%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20share%20buys%20from%20Warburg%20Pincus%20and%20D.V.S.%20Raju%20as%20the%20four%20indicators%20to%20arrive%20at%20Gangavaram%E2%80%99s%20valuation).%20All%20these%20methodologies%2C%20said%20KPMG%2C%20netted%20an%20average%20value%20of%20around%20Rs%20115%20per%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20Adani%20was%20offering%20Rs%20120%20a%20share%2C%20said%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%2C%20both%20SBICaps%20and%20Grant%20Thornton%20Bharat%20LLP%20suggested%20a%20direct%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25022447%2Febidta.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22765%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25022447%2Febidta.jpg%20765w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25022447%2Febidta-300x207.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669697%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22529%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEV%2FEBITDA%20multiples%20of%2014%20%E2%80%9Ccomparable%E2%80%9D%20ports.%20Source%3A%20KPMG%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interview%20to%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20a%20senior%20port%20executive%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20said%20six%20of%20the%2014%20ports%20studied%20by%20KPMG%20were%20state-owned%20ports%20in%20China%20with%20low%20EV%2FEBIDTA%20multiples.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20multiple%20for%20private%20ports%20in%20the%20list%20ran%20as%20high%20as%2023.%20And%2C%20as%20the%20PIL%20said%2C%20two%20other%20international%20ports%20%E2%80%93%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feurobuildcee.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2F27006-dct-gdansk-sold-for-usd-13-bln%5C%22%3E%20DCT%20Gdansk%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20container%20terminal%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-ooil-m-a-macquarie-idUSKCN1S604S%5C%22%3EOrient%20Overseas%20International%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20sold%20at%20EV%2FEBITDA%20multiples%20of%2016%20and%20%E2%80%9Cover%2020%E2%80%9D%20respectively.%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20retains%20a%20record%20of%20this%20and%20other%20interviews%20but%20is%20both%20entitled%20and%20bound%20to%20protect%20its%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20wrote%20to%20Amit%20Jain%20of%20KPMG%20Valuation%20Services%20asking%20why%20he%20thought%20the%20comparison%20they%20had%20made%20was%20valid.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20he%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20the%20debate%20over%20valuation%2C%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20sell%20its%20stake%20in%20the%20first%20place%20has%20also%20been%20questioned.%20The%20state%20had%20given%20land%20many%20years%20ago%20based%20on%20nothing%20but%20a%20DPR%20and%20agreed%20to%20a%20low%20revenue%20share.%20Now%20that%20there%20was%20a%20flourishing%20deep-water%20port%20in%20Gangavaram%2C%20able%20to%20berth%20large%20vessels%2C%20and%20now%20that%20this%20port%20was%20being%20acquired%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20private%20port%20company%2C%20was%20the%20government%20foregoing%20a%20lucrative%20potential%20revenue%20stream%20by%20selling%20its%2010.5%25%20stake%20instead%20of%20holding%20on%20to%20it%20and%20even%20extracting%20better%20terms%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20letter%20to%20CAG%20G.C.%20Murmu%2C%20retired%20IAS%20officer%20E.A.S.%20Sarma%20challenged%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20sell%20its%2010.4%25%20stake%20for%20Rs%20664%20crore%20saying%20that%20even%20back%20in%202017%2C%20the%20port%E2%80%99s%20valuation%20had%20stood%20at%20at%20least%20Rs%207%2C500%20crore%20(i.e.%20%241%20billion%3B%20going%20by%20reports%20of%20Warburg%E2%80%99s%20valuation%20of%20Gangavaram%20at%20between%20%241%20billion%20to%201.4%20billion%20at%20the%20time).%20%E2%80%9CThe%20value%20of%20the%20port%20would%20have%20increased%20since%20then%2C%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20addition%20to%20its%20assets%2C%20its%20increased%20throughput%20and%20the%20increased%20market%20value%20of%20the%201%2C800%20acres%20of%20land%20in%20its%20possession%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcountercurrents.org%2F2023%2F02%2Fap-governments-sale-of-its-equity-share-in-gangavaram-port-to-adani-ports-caused-a-huge-loss-to-public-exchequer-special-audit-called-for%2F%5C%22%3E%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CKeeping%20these%20developments%20in%20view%2C%20the%20state%20government%20ought%20to%20have%20retained%20its%20own%20equity%20share%20in%20the%20port.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20didn%E2%80%99t%20respond%20to%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99s%20questions.%20Its%20arguments%20countering%20the%20PIL%20have%20been%20quoted%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%20also%20asked%20the%20Adani%20Group%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20seemingly%20mismatched%20valuations%20of%20Krishnapatnam%20and%20Gangavaram%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20comparison%20with%20state-owned%20ports.%20In%20its%20statement%2C%20the%20group%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20that%20specific%20question%2C%20saying%20instead%3A%20%E2%80%9COur%20business%20expansion%20decisions%20emerge%20from%20a%20careful%20evaluation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20the%20potential%20acquisition%2C%20its%20prospects%20for%20growth